==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Iatrochemistry
<hw>I*a`tro*chem"is*try</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Chemistry
applied to, or used in, medicine; -- used especially with reference to
the doctrines in the school of physicians in Flanders, in the 17th
century, who held that health depends upon the proper chemical relations
of the fluids of the body, and who endeavored to explain the conditions
of health or disease by chemical principles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iatromathematical</ent>⟦br⟧
